# Security Audit: PE Portfolio Monitor Backend

Auditor: security-reviewer
Date: 2026-04-20
Scope: `/mnt/c/Users/User/Documents/GitHub/claude-squad/pe-portfolio-monitor/backend/`

---

## CRITICAL (Must Fix Before Production)

### 1. No Rate Limiting on `/auth/login` — Brute Force Unmitigated

**Files:** `app/api/auth.py:94-133`

`POST /auth/login` has zero brute-force protection. An attacker can try unlimited password guesses against any known email address with no throttling, lockout, or progressive delay. This is the single highest-risk endpoint in the auth flow.

**Recommendation:** Implement rate limiting (e.g., SlowAPI) at the middleware or dependency level:
- 5 attempts per IP per 15 minutes on `/auth/login`
- Account lockout after 10 failed attempts (temporary, 15 min)
- Return `429 Too Many Requests` when limit is exceeded

