## PASSED CHECKS

### JWT / Auth
- JWT is signed with `HS256` using `settings.SECRET_KEY`
- `SECRET_KEY` loaded from environment with 32-char minimum validation
- Token payload includes `exp`, `iat`, `sub` — no overloading of sensitive data
- `decode_access_token()` returns `None` on any JWTError (fail-closed)
- `create_access_token()` uses `datetime.now(timezone.utc)` (timezone-aware)

### Password Storage
- `app/core/security.py:14` — `CryptContext(schemes=["bcrypt"], deprecated="auto")`
- `hash_password()` and `verify_password()` correctly delegate to bcrypt

### SQL Injection
- All queries use SQLAlchemy's parameterized `select()` / `insert()` / `update()` / `and_()`
- No raw SQL or string interpolation in queries
- `csv_processor.py` uses `csv.DictReader` for parsing (not string splitting)
- UPSERT via PostgreSQL `insert(...).on_conflict_do_update()` — safe

### Tenant Isolation
- `Company`, `AlertRule`, `AuditLog` all use `TenantMixin` (firm_id FK)
- All company-scoped queries filter by `Company.firm_id == user.firm_id`
- `Alert` queries correctly join through `Company` to filter by firm
- `AlertRule` queries filter by `firm_id` explicitly

### RBAC Enforcement
- `require_role()` dependency correctly checks `user.role.value` against `allowed_roles`
- `create_company` — requires `["pe_admin", "pe_ops"]`
- `delete_company` — requires `["pe_admin"]`
- `update_alert`, `evaluate_alerts` — requires `["pe_admin", "pe_ops", "pe_operator", "pe_partner"]`
- `list_companies`, `get_company`, `list_company_metrics` — only require `get_current_user` (firm-scoped)

### CORS
- `app/main.py:27` — `allow_origins=settings.CORS_ORIGINS` (from env)
- Default is restrictive: `["http://localhost:3000", "http://localhost:5173"]`
- Does NOT use `allow_origins=["*"]`
- `allow_credentials=True` is paired with specific origins (safe)

### Input Validation
- Pydantic `EmailStr` on `UserLogin.email`, `UserCreate.email` — format validated
- `uuid.UUID` used for all ID parameters — automatic validation
- `date` types on CSV form fields (`start_date`, `end_date`) — type validated
- `AlertStatus` enum validated against allowed values in `list_alerts`

### CSV Processing
- `csv_processor.py` uses `csv.DictReader` — properly escaped by the csv module
- Numeric conversion via `float(amount_str)` wrapped in try/except — malformed values default to 0.0
- Empty `account_id` rows are skipped (not processed)
- No executable content can be injected via CSV fields

### Secrets Detection
- No hardcoded API keys, OAuth tokens, or refresh tokens in source code
- All credentials sourced from `.env` or database
- `.env` contains only example/development credentials (not production secrets)

